cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use BRACE, please cite the paper and this repository."
title: "BRACE: A Unified Security Framework for Autonomous AI Agents"
abstract: >-
  BRACE is a vendor-neutral control framework for securing autonomous AI
  agents at deployment granularity. It specifies nine controls and three
  observability requirements over an agent's runtime configuration
  (container, harness, system prompt, tool surface, memory, identity,
  network egress), a three-tier adoption order, and a sign-off checklist.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "The BRACE Project"
url: "https://braceframework.org"
repository-code: "https://github.com/brace-ai-security/brace"
license: CC-BY-4.0
keywords:
  - AI security
  - autonomous AI agents
  - agentic AI
  - agent security
  - LLM security
  - prompt injection
  - agent observability
